=3D"583"></use>
</g>
</g>
</svg></span></p><p>The remaining two angles in the triangle are also equal=
 to 60=C2=B0. These are actually <span class=3D"mjpage"><svg xmlns:xlink=3D=
"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width=3D"3.845ex" height=3D"2.843ex" style=
=3D"vertical-align: -0.838ex;" viewBox=3D"0 -863.1 1655.5 1223.9" role=3D"i=
mg" focusable=3D"false" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"MathJax-SVG-3-Title">
<title id=3D"MathJax-SVG-3-Title">\varphi/2</title>
<g stroke=3D"currentColor" fill=3D"currentColor" stroke-width=3D"0" transfo=
rm=3D"matrix(1 0 0 -1 0 0)" aria-hidden=3D"true">
 <use xlink:href=3D"#MJMATHI-3C6" x=3D"0" y=3D"0"></use>
 <use xlink:href=3D"#MJMAIN-2F" x=3D"654" y=3D"0"></use>
 <use xlink:href=3D"#MJMAIN-32" x=3D"1155" y=3D"0"></use>
</g>
</svg></span> because the diagonals of the hexagon (lines connecting opposi=
te vertices) are also axes of symmetry, thus bisecting interior angle <span=
 class=3D"mjpage"><svg xmlns:xlink=3D"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width=
=3D"1.52ex" height=3D"2.176ex" style=3D"vertical-align: -0.838ex;" viewBox=
=3D"0 -576.1 654.5 936.9" role=3D"img" focusable=3D"false" xmlns=3D"http://=
www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-labelledby=3D"MathJax-SVG-4-Title">
<title id=3D"MathJax-SVG-4-Title">\varphi</title>
<g stroke=3D"currentColor" fill=3D"currentColor" stroke-width=3D"0" transfo=
rm=3D"matrix(1 0 0 -1 0 0)" aria-hidden=3D"true">
 <use xlink:href=3D"#MJMATHI-3C6" x=3D"0" y=3D"0"></use>
</g>
</svg></span> (which is 120=C2=B0). Therefore, all the six triangles sharin=
g the center of the hexagon as one of their vertices, are identical equilat=
eral triangles.</p><p>The interior and central angles are also supplementar=
y, since their sum is 180=C2=B0:</p><p><span class=3D"mjpage mjpage__block"=
><svg xmlns:xlink=3D"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width=3D"27.275ex" heigh=
t=3D"2.676ex" style=3D"vertical-align: -0.838ex; margin-left: 3.484ex;" vie=
wBox=3D"0 -791.3 11743.5 1152.1" role=3D"img" focusable=3D"false" xmlns=3D"=
http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-labelledby=3D"MathJax-SVG-5-Title">
