 <use xlink:href=3D"#MJMATHI-3B1" x=3D"0" y=3D"0"></use>
</g>
</svg></span> and also among each other. These relationships can be discove=
red using the properties of the right triangle, whose sides are: the circum=
radius, the inradius and half the hexagon side, as highlighted in the figur=
e below. Using basic trigonometry we find:</p><p><span class=3D"mjpage mjpa=
ge__block"><svg xmlns:xlink=3D"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width=3D"15.15=
